author: Keiko Morris
title: Google Parent to Buy Manhattan’s Chelsea Market Building in $2 Billion Deal
text:
The parent company of Google is expanding its real-estate holdings in Manhattan, with plans to plow more than $2 billion into one of the city’s prime tech neighborhoods. 
Under the deal, Alphabet Inc. entered a contract to buy the Chelsea Market building at 75 Ninth Ave. from Jamestown LP, according to a person familiar with the transaction.
